WHILE LOOP:  This loop executes while the condition is true.

while (condition is true) 
{
  //code goes here
}

DO WHILE LOOP: This loop executes at least once and may execute multiple times while the condition is true.

do
{
   //code goes here
}
while (condition is true);

FOR LOOP:  This loop executes repeatedly until a condition becomes false.  

for(int var = starting value; var <= ending value; var++)
{
   //code goes here
}

FOR EACH LOOP:  This loop iterates through each of the elements within a collection. 

foreach(Element Type element in collection)
{
     //code goes here
}

